The paper deals with algorithmic issues in situations where the objects under investigation are not accessible due to various limitations, which is a common problem in many fields including physics, biochemistry, economics, and computer science. The paper proposes a trial-and-error model to examine these issues, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also deals with constraint satisfaction problems, which are a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses order theory and strong ellipsoid method, which are topics in game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
